Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer
exclusive Copyright and Related Rights (defined below) upon the creator and
subsequent owner(s) (each and all, an "owner") of an original work of
authorship and/or a database (each, a "Work").

The owner(s) of such Work often use the exclusive rights granted to them by
Copyright and Related Rights to control the use and distribution of the Work.
By choosing to share the Work in a public manner, the owner(s) grant the public
certain permissions to use the Work. The purpose of this license is to allow
the public to use the Work with as few restrictions as possible.

The person(s) releasing this Work (the "Affirmer") either holds the Copyright
and Related Rights in the Work or is authorized by the owner(s) to release this
Work under this CC0 1.0 Universal license.

For the purposes of this public license, "Copyright and Related Rights" means
all rights provided by copyright law and related rights, including but not
limited to:
 1. the right to reproduce, adapt, distribute, perform, display, communicate,
    and translate a Work;
 2. moral rights retained by the original author(s) and/or performer(s);
 3. publicity and privacy rights pertaining to a person's image or likeness
    depicted in a Work;
 4. rights protecting against unfair competition in regards to a Work;
 5. rights protecting the extraction, dissemination, use and reuse of data in
    a Work;
 6. database rights (such as those arising under Directive 96/9/EC of the
    European Parliament and of the Council of 11 March 1996 on the legal
    protection of databases, and under any national implementation thereof);
 7. other similar, equivalent or corresponding rights throughout the world
    based on applicable law or treaty, and any national implementations thereof.

